The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Tapping law

 New Delhi, Feb. 25: The Centre has decided to amend the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885, to check unauthorised interception of telephone conversations, reports our legal correspondent.

 In an affidavit before the Supreme Court, the home ministry said the government proposed to make certain provisions in the act more stringent. The matter will come up for hearing on Monday.




